content.description: Mount Dickey is one of the most impressive peaks in the Ruth Gorge.  It's east face is so enormous that it's hard to comprehend that it is actually a mile wide and 5000' tall.  There are numerous routes on the south and east faces of this mountain but they are all very serious and committing.  A more reasonable route to the top is via the west face which is a moderate 35 to 40 degree snow climb.  For strong experienced parties there is still a lot of new route potential on this mountain.
